i  {		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    environment.systemPackages = [		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      pkgs.nyancat		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    ];		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  }		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iIt adds the subobject `nyancat` of parameter `pkgs` (also an object)		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ito the list of `environment.systemPackages` . `pkgs` is the collection		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iof all packages in the NixOS package repository, defined at		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
hhttps://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs	URL:https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs	{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i. Similarly, `config` is the collection of all config parameters. If		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iyou want the list of all installed packages, you can use `config.environment.systemPackages` .		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i> Nix language uses lazy evaluation. NixOS won't do anything right		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i> after loading the config file. A config item (e.g. `environment.systemPackages` )		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i> will only have its value parsed (the array, as well as the object `pkgs.nyancat` )		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i> when it's referenced.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i> 		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i> By the way, the Nix language doesn't support circular references.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i> Config like `{ a = config.b; b = config.a; }` won't work and will		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i> error out with `infinite recursion encountered` .		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
